❗️The State Power Committee considered the proposals of local self-government bodies, military administrations, the Ukrainian Institute of National Memory, the National Commission for State Language Standards on the renaming of settlements and districts, the names of which contain symbols of Russian imperial policy or do not meet the standards of the state language, in order to bring the names into compliance with the Law of Ukraine "On condemnation and prohibition of propaganda of Russian imperial policy in Ukraine and decolonization of toponymy" of the following regions: Dnipropetrovsk, Donetsk, Zaporizhzhia, Kyiv, Kirovohrad, Luhansk, Lviv, Mykolaiv, Odesa, Poltava, Sumy, Kharkiv, Kherson, Khmelnytsky, Cherkasy, Chernihiv The Committee, in particular:

- supported the renaming of three cities, 149 settlements and villages, seven districts;
- instructed the members of the Committee to develop and submit to the Parliament a draft Resolution "On renaming certain settlements and districts";
- recommended adopting the draft Resolution as a whole. 📲 Details and list

