❗️The Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine adopted in the first reading the project of the Law of Ukraine on the introduction of the institution of conditional early release of persons from serving a sentence for their direct participation in the defense of the country (No. 11079-1). The purpose is to determine the legal and organizational basis for the involvement in military service of citizens convicted for committing crimes.

In particular, the act proposes to provide for the possibility of parole during mobilization and martial law, except for persons who have been convicted of:

 - crimes against the national security of Ukraine;
 - committing particularly serious crimes;
 - criminal offenses against sexual freedom and sexual integrity of a person;
 - terrorism;
 - Fatal road accident under the influence of drugs or alcohol.

It is also proposed to establish criminal liability for evasion of military service under a contract by a person who was released conditionally - early from serving a sentence for military service. 📲Details

